    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|><|channel>thought\n<channel|>It's hard to \"pick myself up\" when there's nothing to stand on. Every time I try to fix one thing, three more things break. The interest, the collectors, the sheer amount of it... it feels like a physical weight on my chest. It's not just stress, it's like looking at a wall that's just closing in on me. I don't see a \"bigger picture,\" I just see a dead end.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
